         <h2>PLSS in Google Earth (PLSGE)</h2>

      The principal component of PLSGE is a Google Earth implementation of the
      Public Land Survey System (<a target="_blank"
      href="http://nationalmap.gov/small_scale/a_plss.html">PLSS</a>)
      Cadastral National Spatial Data Infrastructure (<a target="_blank"
      href="https://nationalcad.org/download/PublicationHandbookOct2016.pdf">PLSS CadNSDI</a>)
      <a target="_blank"
      href="https://gis.blm.gov/arcgis/rest/services/Cadastral/BLM_Natl_PLSS_CadNSDI/MapServer/">map
      service</a>.
      It retrieves multiresolution images of the PLSS from the
      Bureau of Land Management (<a target="_blank" href="https://www.blm.gov/">BLM</a>) .
      <ol><li>
         Position the area of interest (AOI) in the viewer.
         </li><li>
         Check the radio button beside the <i>Alaska SDMS</i>, <i>Townships</i>,
         or <i>Special Surveys</i> network link. Use the <i>Townships</i> overlay to find
         townships and sections. Use the <i>Special Surveys</i> overlay to find other divisions.
         </li><li>
         On subsequent uses, reposition the AOI and ensure that the network link
         is checked and selected.
         When <i>Refresh Mode</i> is <i>Automatic</i>, the
         overlay is refreshed two seconds after camera movement stops.
         When <i>Refresh Mode</i> is <i>Manual</i>, choose <i>Refresh</i>
         from the <i>Edit</i> menu, or right-click
         and select <i>Refresh</i> in the context menu
         (<a href="/RefreshNetworkLink.html">explain</a>).
      </li></ol>
      Coverage includes Alabama, Alaska, Arizona, Arkansas, California, Colorado, Florida, Idaho,
      Illinois, Indiana, Iowa, Kansas, Louisiana, Michigan, Minnesota, Mississippi, Missouri,
      Montana, Nebraska, Nevada, New Mexico, North Dakota, Ohio, Oklahoma, Oregon, South Dakota,
      Utah, Washington, Wisconsin, and Wyoming.
      <p>
      PLSGE also includes protracted townships provided by the Alaska Spatial Data Management System
      (<a target="_blank"
      href="https://sdms.ak.blm.gov/sdms/index.html">SDMS</a>) and a facility
      to draw approximate PLSS boundaries with links to BLM <a target="_blank"
      href="https://www.glorecords.blm.gov/">land records</a>.
      <p>
      All images and data are retrieved from remote servers. Data errors,
      accuracy, and availability are beyond the control of this application.
      <p>
